[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 to WHO remains at 215.

Data by country, area, or territory for 18 Sep 2020 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/WHO%20daily%20tablesSept18_1600467953.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 37.9% of daily case numbers and 56.5% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, maintaining its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 15.2 million cases. The USA and Brazil remain dominant, followed by Argentina, Colombia, Peru and Mexico. Other countries reporting more than 1000 new cases in the past 24 hours include Chile, Costa Rica, Paraguay, and Honduras.

- The European region reported 21.0% of daily case numbers and 11.5% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 5 million. Countries not reporting cases today (18 Sep 2020) include Belgium and Sweden. The dominant country is Spain, followed by France, Israel, Russia, the UK, Ukraine, and the Czech Republic. Other countries reporting more than 1000 new cases in the past 24 hours include Germany, the Netherlands, Romania, Turkey, and Italy.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 5.6% of daily case numbers and 6.5% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of greater than 2.1 million cases. Iraq remains the dominant country, followed by Iran, Morocco, Palestinian Authority, Libya, Kuwait, the UAE, Pakistan, Bahrain, Lebanon, and Saudi Arabia.

- The African region reported 1.5% of daily case numbers and 1.9% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours and has reported more than 1.1 million cases. South Africa is again the dominant country, followed by Ethiopia, Kenya, Algeria, Mozambique, Nigeria, Uganda, Namibia, Angola, and Botswana.

- The Western Pacific region reported 1.3% of daily case numbers and 1.3% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of 0.56 million cases. The Philippines continues to dominate, followed by Japan, South Korea, and China.

- The South East Asia region reported 32.7% of the daily newly reported cases and 22.4% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 5.7 million cases. India continues to dominate followed by Indonesia, Bangladesh, Nepal, and Myanmar.

Europe is experiencing resurgences in many countries related to loosening restrictions and the summer vacation period. Major transmission is ongoing in South East Asia, specifically India, with record-breaking daily case reports.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 18 Sep 2020 is an excellent visual representation of the epidemic. - Mod.MPP]

