[The USA, India, and Brazil are still the most severely affected countries in terms of cumulative case counts and daily new case confirmations, with India now in the 2nd position followed by Brazil. In the past 24 hours, these 3 countries -- India (92 769), followed by the USA (51 345) and Brazil (39 991) -- account for over half of all confirmed cases globally (54.5%) and 52.4% of all newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours. A global total of 5991 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (17-18 Sep 2020).

Countries reporting more than 5000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours include India, USA, Brazil, Spain (33 683), France (13 215), Peru (12 012), Argentina (11 945), Colombia (6526), and Russia (5905), and 33 countries have reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours. Five of the 10 top countries reporting the highest daily newly confirmed cases are from the Americas region; 8 of the top 20 countries reporting the highest daily newly confirmed cases are from the European region. Also, 13 of the 33 countries reporting more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours are in the European region, and 10 of these 33 countries are in the Americas region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, there is an increase in case counts by 9.5%, while daily reported deaths have decreased by 9.8%.

Impression: Cases are increasing globally, with Europe showing major increasing transmission in many countries and the Americas region as well. - Mod.MPP]
